==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|ˌɑɻ.kiˈɔl.ʌ.ʤi}}
ARK-ee-OL-o-gy
Ar*chae-o*lo-gy

===Etymology===
Greek ''archa&iacute;os'' (ancient) + [[λόγος]] (study).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|archaeolog|ies}}

#The [[scientific]] [[study]] of the [[material]] [[remains]] of the [[past]] and of the [[life]] and [[culture]] of [[ancient]] [[peoples]]. One of the four [[sub]]-[[discipline]]s of [[anthropology]].

====Spelling variants====
*'''archæology'''
*'''archeology''' (primarily USA)

